    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A Japanese metalworking process which produces a mixed-metal laminate with distinctive layered patterns. Mokume-gane translates closely to "wood grain metal" or "wood eye metal" and describes the way metal takes on the appearance of natural wood grain.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
